WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.360
AhaSlides has two language settings — one for the presenter, one for the audience.

00:00:04.500 --> 00:00:07.690
Click the globe icon to change the presenter interface language.

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:11.890
Pick from 27 interface languages — the app switches instantly.

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
The audience language is in presentation Settings. Click New presentation.

00:00:16.500 --> 00:00:19.190
Click Poll to add a slide — then we'll open Settings.

00:00:20.500 --> 00:00:25.750
The Poll slide is in your deck. Now let's open Settings to set the audience display language.

00:00:26.000 --> 00:00:28.120
Click the Settings icon on the right panel.

00:00:28.500 --> 00:00:32.340
The Settings panel is opening — you'll see options for your entire presentation.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:35.120
In Settings, click Presentation language.

00:00:35.500 --> 00:00:40.460
Navigating to the Presentation language tab — here you'll find the dropdown for your audience's language.

00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:44.600
Pick from 32 languages — your audience sees the change immediately.

00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:47.870
The language is saved automatically. Let's close Settings.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:53.380
Click Preview to see exactly what your audience will see when you go live — including the language you just set.

00:00:53.500 --> 00:00:56.000
Your audience sees AhaSlides in their chosen language — questions, options, and the join screen all in their language.
